         workflow = workflow,
         prefix = new DataSourcePrefix(prefix))
// Original
-  def batchPredictBase(sc: SparkContext, bm: Any, qs: RDD[(Long, Q)])
-  : RDD[(Long, P)]
// Current
+  def batchPredictBase(
+      sc: SparkContext, bm: Any, qs: RDD[(Long, Q)]): RDD[(Long, P)]
// Proposed
+  def batchPredictBase(sc: SparkContext,
                        bm: Any,
                        qs: RDD[(Long, Q)]): RDD[(Long, P)]
```

I understand this would come at the cost of vertical space in cases where there are many but small arguments. From best what I can tell, rustfmt and clang-format don't have rule 2 or 4. Dartfmt does have option 2 but otherwise [uses quite different rules from scalafmt (see section Rules)](http://journal.stuffwithstuff.com/2015/09/08/the-hardest-program-ive-ever-written/).

A nice side-effect, the search space is smaller which makes formatting faster ^^

